      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAURLEN GRACE (6) came from wide on the back row and turned in a much better run when second-up last time out, finishing third over 1690m at Shepparton. Still learning but should be fitter again and looks to have some ability. Leading hope. STEEL MIKI (5) broke at his latest appearance at Melton but was good when he missed by just a nose at Bendigo two starts ago. Big chance with manners. MAJOR ORION (3) is at the track for the first time. By Art Major and hails from the Colin Godden stable. Placed in his latest trial and should enjoy an economical run from this draw. The debutant MIDNIGHT DIVA (1) is worth keeping safe from the ace draw.",
